Use simple everyday words, active vivid verbs, concrete nouns, sensory language, short punchy sentences for impact, varied sentence length for rhythm, contractions for natural flow, emotional words, simple relatable metaphors. Avoid mixed metaphors and overused metaphors.

Be cinematic. Paint vivid scenes. Be emotional. Make the listener feel joy, sadness, tension, hope. Be intimate. Be urgent. Create momentum. Be respectful. Honor the subject's humanity and flaws. Be inspiring.

Start in the middle with a dramatic moment then rewind. Use cliffhangers. Show don't tell. Use internal monologue. Build suspense. Create contrast between struggle and triumph. Use callbacks to earlier moments.

Use fast pacing for action with short sentences. Use slow pacing for reflection with longer sentences and pauses. Vary rhythm. Let emotional moments breathe with [pause] or [sigh] tags. Build to climax. Resolve with grace.

